quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  26,1,Sin. Mim
  26,2,These are the signs of the clear Book
  26,3,Perhaps thou dost torment thyself that they are not believers
  26,4,"If We will, We will send down a sign from Heaven and their heads would remain bowed before it in humility"
  26,5,"Yet no new reminder comes to them from the Compassionate, but that they turn away from it"
  26,6,"Indeed, they have denied it, but there shall come to them the tidings of that which they used to mock"
  26,7,"Have they not considered the earth, how much of every noble kind We have caused to grow therein"
  26,8,"Truly in that is a sign, but most of them are not believers"
  26,9,"And truly thy Lord is the Mighty, the Merciful"